### Housing Signal Direction (GROWTH Category Override)

For GROWTH events (housing, GDP, retail sales), direction logic is DIFFERENT from INFLATION:

| Signal | SPY | TLT | Rationale |
|--------|-----|-----|-----------|
| DOVISH (weak housing) | **‚Üì** | ‚Üë | Weak growth = risk-off ‚Üí equities DOWN, bonds UP |
| HAWKISH (strong housing) | **‚Üë** | ‚Üì | Strong growth = risk-on ‚Üí equities UP, bonds DOWN |

> This is the OPPOSITE of INFLATION signals where DOVISH ‚Üí SPY‚Üë (rate cuts = bullish).
> Backtested: 4/4 housing releases confirm this pattern.

